# Copy to `.env` and fill in to enable the live LLM (OpenAI-compatible Chat Completions API).
# Any non-empty key enables real requests; use a dummy value for local Ollama.
VITE_OPENAI_API_KEY=
# Optional overrides:
# VITE_OPENAI_BASE_URL=https://api.openai.com/v1
# VITE_OPENAI_MODEL=gpt-4o-mini

# --- Ollama (local, OpenAI-compatible `/v1/chat/completions`) ---
# 1) Install Ollama, then: ollama pull <your-model>   (use the exact name from `ollama list`)
# 2) Dev server proxies /api/ollama → Ollama (see vite.config.ts), so use:
# VITE_OPENAI_API_KEY=ollama
# VITE_OPENAI_BASE_URL=/api/ollama/v1
# VITE_OPENAI_MODEL=qwen3.5
# If you call Ollama directly instead of the proxy, set base to http://127.0.0.1:11434/v1
# and ensure Ollama allows your dev origin (e.g. OLLAMA_ORIGINS) if the browser blocks CORS.
